body:
A multi-bit bus can be indexed dynamically with a multi-bit input, however, when I try to write a 1 to one bit of a bus in the example below, nothing happens. Replacing `bus[bus_index] <= 1'b1;` with `bus[8] <= 1'b1;` does write a 1 to that bit.

Although this example uses Symbiyosys, I'm fairly confident that this is a yosys issue because there is a specific commit (15eb66b99dc40901895d4e4a512d3c49dde3a9b4) that touches the LHS bus assignment logic. Using a version of yosys built before this commit properly writes the 1 to the bit specified by bus_index, and using a version of yosys built after this commit does not.

All source files, including the yosys model files and Symbiyosys log files are attached. In the case where this formal test fails, `bus` is initialized to all 0s.

## Steps to reproduce the issue

- Install Symbiyosys and dependencies
- Create a directory that contains these two files:
bus_writer_formal.sby
```
[options]
mode bmc
depth 50

[engines]
smtbmc

[script]
read -formal bus_writer_formal.sv
prep -top bus_writer_formal

[files]
bus_writer_formal.sv
```
bus_writer_formal.sv
```
module bus_writer_formal(
   CORE_CLK,
   write_bus,
   bus_index
);

   input          CORE_CLK;
   input          write_bus;
   input [3:0]    bus_index;

   reg   [6:0]    free_counter;
   reg   [15:0]   bus;
   reg            check_assertions;

   initial free_counter = '0;
   initial bus = '0;

   //check assertions if the bus should have been written
   //and the bus write happened after the first few clock
   //cycles, avoiding any potential weirdness at time=0
   initial check_assertions = 0;

   always@(posedge CORE_CLK) begin
      if(write_bus) begin
         bus[bus_index] <= 1'b1;
         check_assertions <= (free_counter > 'd1);
      end
      else begin
         check_assertions <= 1'b0;
      end

      free_counter <= free_counter + 1;

      //if(check_assertions) assert(bus[$past(bus_index)] == 1'b1);
      if(check_assertions) assert(|bus == 1'b1);

      cover(|bus == 1'b1);
   end
endmodule
```
- Build yosys at commit hash 15eb66b99dc40901895d4e4a512d3c49dde3a9b4 or later
- Run `sby bus_writer_formal.sby`

The formal test should fail and produce a waveform that looks like the one below. Asserting `write_bus` should write a 1 to some bit in `bus`, but `bus` remains all 0s.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/93947161/170784365-0bf8dbd0-2d0f-44cf-ad7d-dbdd2c9e09a7.png)

Running the test in cover mode (using `mode cover` instead of `mode bmc` in bus_writer_formal.sby) does show that bus can be written when `bus_index` is 4'b0. The test passes in cover mode.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/93947161/170786990-ba3f3a26-6c36-4ee2-a53e-8b714f3a648d.png)

## Expected behavior

One cycle after `write_bus` goes high, one or more bits in `bus` should be 1. The Symbiyosys BMC formal test should pass.

## Actual behavior

When `bus` is initialized to all 0s, one cycle after `write_bus` goes high, `bus` is still all 0s. The Symbiyosys BMC formal test fails.

[bus_writer_yosys_example.zip](https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys/files/8789198/bus_writer_yosys_example.zip)

